According to the lack of numerical researches concentrating on the appraisal of irreversibility in ETSCs, this study is fixated on analyzing the irreversibly inside an open thermosyphon solar collector aim to extract the efficacy of entropy generation on the productivity of suggested unit. Furthermore, a comparative evaluation between the two cases by utilization of pure water and nanofluid are presented over 1 h of the simulation process. CuO-H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
