The modeling technique has been employed for a close-ended thermosyphon ETSC along with the manifold investigating its thermal behavior and entropy generation. Figure 1 provides an overview of the geometry of the simulated model. As exhibited in this graph, the absorber tube was divided into 3 vertical sections that aim to analyze the flow array within the absorber, from the entrance section toward the close-end. The absorber tube has been considered with a slope of 45 ∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
